1. Prepare files in HDFS with required permissions (mkdir /demo/training/input)
2. Copy data through HDFS web view
3. Create Maven project
4. Add repository and dependencies
5. Add main class
6. Build jar
7. Copy jar with WinSCP tool in executable directory (/home/bigdata)
8. Run jar with command "hadoop jar hadoop-1.jar WordCount /demo/training/input /demo/training/output"
9. Don't forget       job.setJarByClass(WordCount.class); if ClassNotFoundException
10. Implement Tool interface (it makes your code more configurable)